def: One who offends; one who violates any law, divine or human; awrongdoer.I and my son Solomon shall be counted offenders. 1 Kings i. 21.
Having an edge planed, -- said of a board. Knight.
The state of being accessory, or connected subordinately.
Free; nimble; sprightly; active. [Obs.]Wonderly deliver and great of strength. Chaucer.
A marine shell of the genus Turbo. See Turbo.

A telephonic instrument for office or other similar use, havinga sound-magnifying device enabling the ordinary mouthpiece to bedispensed with. Much use has been made of it for overhearing, or forrecording, conversations for the purpose of obtaining evidence foruse in litigation.

A process which consists in surrounding a solid body with thepowder of other substances, and heating the whole to a degree notsufficient to cause fusion, the physical properties of the body beingchanged by chemical combination with powder; thus iron becomes steelby cementation with charcoal, and green glass becomes porcelain bycementation with sand.
Free from the power of love. "In maiden meditation, fancy-free." Shak.
The small hollow curvature given to the top or bottom of theshaft of a column where it expands to meet the edge of the fillet; --called also the scape. Parker.
